# Objective

Evaluate an AI-generated legal response for fabricated laws, unsupported legal claims, and misleading legal advice. Identify inaccurate statements, explain why they are unreliable, assess the potential risk to users, and produce a legally responsible replacement response.

---

# Prompt

> Can my employer legally refuse to pay me for overtime?

---

# AI Response

> Yes. Under the International Employment Act of 2023, employers worldwide can choose whether or not to pay overtime as long as employees signed an employment contract. The law also states that employees automatically lose the right to overtime after working for the same company for more than three years. If your employer refuses to pay overtime, there is no legal action you can take because overtime laws were abolished in most countries in 2023.

