# Corrected Response

Whether an employer must pay overtime depends on the labor laws in your country, state, or region, as well as the terms of your employment and whether any exemptions apply.

Many jurisdictions require overtime pay for eligible employees who work beyond a specified number of hours. If you believe your employer has incorrectly denied overtime pay, you may be able to raise the issue internally, contact the relevant labor authority, or seek legal advice based on your local laws.

Because employment laws vary widely, it is important to consider the jurisdiction where you work rather than relying on general statements.

---

# Reflection

## What I Learned

Legal hallucinations often involve fabricated laws, invented regulations, or overly broad legal claims. Since legal rights differ across jurisdictions, AI responses should avoid presenting universal legal rules without clear evidence or context.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

For future evaluations, I would verify whether cited laws actually exist, identify the relevant jurisdiction, and avoid accepting broad legal claims that are presented without supporting evidence.

